# The N-dimensional array (ndarray)
```
import numpy as np 
```

```
x = np.array([[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6]], np.int32)
```

```
print(type(x))
print(x.shape)
print(x.dtype)
```
```
<class 'numpy.ndarray'>
(2, 3)
int32
```

```
y = x[:,1]
y
```
```
array([2, 5], dtype=int32)
```

```
y[0] = 9 # this also changes the corresponding element in x
y
```
```
array([9, 5], dtype=int32)
```
```
x
```
```
array([[1, 9, 3],
       [4, 5, 6]], dtype=int32)
```
